5:
Your name is Seiji Takamori... and
you're a teacher?
9:
A middle school teacher to be
precise. I'm currently Nao's teacher...
12:
And I used to be yours, Shota's, and
Yuki's when you were middle
schoolers.
15:
...So you've lost your memories.
Based on what I've heard, it sounds
like a case of generalized amnesia.
19:
However, it's strange that your
semantic memory is also affected.
You've forgotten what should be
basic knowledge and vocabulary.
23:
Wow, Mr. Takamori, you're like a
walking search engine!
26:
I'm afraid I only have passing
knowledge on the subject. It would
be better if you had someone
examine you, but... I highly doubt
we'll find anyone qualified here.
30:
...Could you give me a more detailed
account about what happened to
the city?
38:
Nuh-uh. You call me Nao. That's how
it's supposed to be.
42:
R-right... I'd also like to know about
our parents.
47:
There was an earthquake about
three months ago. I remember I was
preparing for our closing ceremony
before winter break.
50:
The strange thing is, it wasn't
tremors that hit first—it was a
blinding light...
54:
The sky turned pure white. I thought
for sure a missile had finally come
for us.
58:
Yeah? I thought it was a meteor
about to end the world.
63: Huh... Well, I thought it was a kaiju.
66:
O-only for a second! Something
roared and... it sounded like a kaiju
from one of Dad's favorite movies.
71:
Then the earthquake happened. It
wasn't pretty, but it also wasn't
horrendous. We realized the bigger
issue afterward.
75:
All of us had become trapped in this
city.
82:
Anyone who tries to leave Shibuya
ends up never coming back.
87:
Dad was one of them. He just left to
get supplies without thinking about
it...
91:
After a while, Mom got worried and
went searching for him, and then...
96:
I bet your mom was looking for you
too, Ayumu.
106:
It's been a rough situation for
everyone. I shudder to imagine how
much worse it would've been
without the Starsayers.
111:
Ah, right, those people that've been
on guard duty. What exactly have
they been protecting you from?
114:
Mostly people that have taken to
pillaging and controlling others
through force.
118:
Those Aegis punks took care of the
yakuza and stuff at the start, but...
121:
Then they started attacking us too.
Talk about a dick move, huh?
125:
Instead of banding together,
everyone went for each other's
throats...
130: Was Alk here three months ago?
135:
Y-yeah! We were getting by just fine,
but then one day, he left for cram
school...
139:
...Yet three months ago, Alk was with
us. We met more than a year prior.
144:
I recognize this town though. So time
really does pass differently...
164:
Go and hide inside! The Aegis boy
with the shadows is here!
168:
With the shadows... It's gotta be that
guy again!
174:
You're not seriously going to go out
there, are you? Why put yourself in
danger like that?
178:
I'm not going to sit by while I can do
something to help!
188: We'd just get in the way...
197:
Preaching all that crap about hope
and equality. You really think people
at the bottom of the food chain get
rights?
199:
Hey, Ryuichi! Why'd you bother
coming? We coulda handled this
ourselves easy!
202: ...The real fight is about to start.
209:
What's the point of all this violence?
They're people too, just like you and
me!
212:
Pffft, who are these cosplaying
weirdos? Ryuichi, did this kid really
kick your ass earlier?
214:
We'll take care of this, so why don't
you give us a little boost, Ryuichi?
228:
Hahaha! Guess we're the bad guys
in this guy's roleplay!
230:
Better make sure we play the part
perfectly!
